{
	"description": "Here we have added the otkmodal-isvisible class to the otkmodal div as well as the motkmodal-backdrop-isvisible class to the backdrop to show both the modal and the backdrop.  We have commented out both as they will make the documentation look odd, but you must add these class names and set display:block on the otkmodal div in order to make your modals appear",
	"html": "<!--<div class=\"otkmodal otkmodal-isvisible\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\" role=\"dialog\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" aria-hidden=\"false\" style=\"display:block\"> -->\n\n    <!-- this div below determines if the modal is actually a modal, it is the backdrop that masks the page -->\n    <!-- <div class=\"otkmodal-backdrop otkmodal-backdrop-isvisible\"></div> -->\n    <div class=\"otkmodal-dialog otkmodal-md\">\n        <a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" class=\"otkmodal-close\" data-dismiss=\"otkmodal\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n            <i class=\"otkicon otkicon-closecircle\"></i>\n        </a>\n        <div class=\"otkmodal-content\">\n            <div class=\"otkmodal-header\">\n                <h4 class=\"otkmodal-title otktitle-2\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Log In To Origin</h4>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"otkmodal-body\">...</div>\n            <div class=\"otkmodal-footer\">\n                <a href=\"#\" class=\"otkbtn otkbtn-primary\">Click Me!</a>\n                <a href=\"#\" class=\"otkbtn otkbtn-light\">Do it</a>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n<!-- </div> -->"
}